---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "Genshin Tier List - Meta Rankings & Analysis",
  description: "Are you investing resources into the wrong characters? Our comprehensive Genshin Tier List reveals the optimal meta compositions you need to clear the...",
  category: "list",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
    {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why are some 4-star characters ranked higher than 5-star characters?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "In Genshin Impact, rarity does not always equal power. Several 4-star characters released at the game's launch (specifically Bennett, Xingqiu, Xiangling, and Fischl) have foundational kits that provide massive utility, off-field damage, and elemental application. They outclass many 5-stars because their abilities synergize perfectly with the core elemental reaction system."
        }
    },
    {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need C6 4-stars or C1 5-stars to follow this tier list?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "This tier list assumes C0 for limited 5-star characters and C0 for standard banner 5-stars. For 4-star characters, it assumes they have their most critical constellations (usually C2-C4) since they are much easier to obtain over time. However, top-tier units like Bennett and Xingqiu are still incredibly powerful even at C0."
        }
    },
    {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why did my favorite character drop in the tier list this patch?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The Genshin meta revolves around the Spiral Abyss, which changes enemy lineups and buffs every patch. If the new Abyss features enemies with high resistance to your character's element, or if a new artifact set/support character drastically buffs a competing unit, your character's relative ranking will drop, even if their personal damage hasn't changed."
        }
    },
    {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is it worth pulling for a weapon banner to make my character higher tier?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Generally, no. A character's signature 5-star weapon usually provides a 15-25% damage increase over their best 4-star or free-to-play option. However, pulling a new top-tier support character (like Nahida or Kazuha) will provide a much larger overall damage increase to your entire team than a single weapon upgrade."
        }
    },
    {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I clear the Spiral Abyss with low-tier characters?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, absolutely. Every character in Genshin Impact can clear floor 12 of the Spiral Abyss with enough investment in their artifacts, talents, and team synergy. Higher-tier characters simply make the process faster, require less optimal artifacts, and are more forgiving of player mistakes."
        }
    }
]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": meta.title,
    "description": meta.description,
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "SiliconBased"
    },
    "datePublished": meta.published
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout site="siliconbased" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/genshin-tier-list" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Genshin Tier List</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Complete Character Rankings & Meta Analysis</p>
    </div>


    <div class="tier-container">
      <div class="tier-row">
        <div class="tier-label ss">SS</div>
        <div class="tier-content">
          <span class="char-badge">Neuvillette</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Furina</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Nahida</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Kazuha</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Yelan</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Zhongli</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Raiden Shogun</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-row">
        <div class="tier-label s">S</div>
        <div class="tier-content">
          <span class="char-badge">Alhaitham</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Hu Tao</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Xingqiu</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Bennett</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Xiangling</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Kokomi</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Baizhu</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Navia</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-row">
        <div class="tier-label a">A</div>
        <div class="tier-content">
          <span class="char-badge">Ayaka</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Tartaglia</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Nilou</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Wriothesley</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Lyney</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Yae Miko</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Fischl</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Kuki Shinobu</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-row">
        <div class="tier-label b">B</div>
        <div class="tier-content">
          <span class="char-badge">Ganyu</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Xiao</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Wanderer</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Cyno</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Yoimiya</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Ayato</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Venti</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Sucrose</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-row">
        <div class="tier-label c">C</div>
        <div class="tier-content">
          <span class="char-badge">Eula</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Klee</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Diluc</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Keqing</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Dehya</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Qiqi</span>
          <span class="char-badge">Aloy</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <p>Navigating the complex character ecosystem of Teyvat can be incredibly daunting. With new updates releasing every six weeks, the meta is constantly shifting. Characters who were once considered absolute necessities fall by the wayside, while previously overlooked 4-stars suddenly find new life thanks to the release of a synergistic artifact set or a new elemental reaction. Understanding a Genshin tier list is not about strictly adhering to a rigid set of rules; rather, it is about understanding resource management, team synergy, and the current demands of the Spiral Abyss.</p>

      <p>In Genshin Impact, your most valuable resources are not Primogems, but Resin and time. Building a single character to their maximum potential—leveling them to 90, crowning their talents, and farming a cohesive artifact set with optimal sub-stats—can take weeks or even months of dedicated farming. Therefore, knowing which characters provide the highest return on investment is crucial for both free-to-play players and dedicated spenders. A well-constructed Genshin tier list serves as a roadmap, helping you prioritize your resin expenditure and construct teams that can effortlessly clear the game's hardest content.</p>

      <h2>How We Evaluate Characters</h2>
      <p>Creating a definitive Genshin tier list is notoriously difficult because character power is heavily dependent on context. A character who is mediocre at Constellation 0 (C0) might become a powerhouse at Constellation 6 (C6). A niche support might be completely useless on 90% of teams but absolutely critical for the remaining 10%. To provide a balanced and actionable list, we evaluate characters based on a specific set of criteria designed to reflect the average player's experience in the current endgame meta.</p>

      <p>First and foremost, we look at versatility. Characters like Kaedehara Kazuha or Yelan sit at the very top of the Genshin tier list because they can be slotted into almost any team composition and immediately elevate its performance. They are "plug-and-play" units that provide massive account value. Secondly, we evaluate pure damage potential, but only within the context of team DPS. Genshin Impact is a game of elemental reactions, not solo hyper-carries. A character's individual damage ceiling is less important than their ability to enable or capitalize on powerful reactions like Vaporize, Aggravate, or Hyperbloom.</p>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>The Support Supremacy Rule:</strong><br>
        In the long-term Genshin meta, <em>Supports > Sub-DPS > Main DPS.</em><br>
        A top-tier Main DPS will eventually be power-crept by a newer unit, but a top-tier Support like Bennett or Nahida will remain relevant indefinitely because they elevate the damage of the entire roster.
      </div>

      <h2>The SS Tier: The Meta Defining Archons and Supports</h2>
      <p>The characters in the SS tier are the undisputed kings and queens of the meta. These are the units that fundamentally alter how you play the game. If you have the opportunity to pull for these characters, they should be your absolute highest priority, regardless of what the rest of your roster looks like.</p>

      <p>At the pinnacle of this tier sit the premier supports and sub-DPS units. Nahida, the Dendro Archon, is essentially mandatory for any Dendro-based team (Hyperbloom, Aggravate, Bloom) due to her unmatched elemental application and massive Elemental Mastery buffs. Furina has completely reshaped the meta by providing universal damage bonuses that rival even the most specialized supports, while also offering excellent off-field damage and healing capabilities. Neuvillette, a rare Main DPS in this tier, earns his spot simply by outputting such absurd, self-sustaining area-of-effect damage that he can often clear the Spiral Abyss entirely on his own without a team.</p>

      <p>Then we have the timeless classics: Kazuha, Yelan, and Zhongli. Kazuha provides unmatched crowd control and elemental damage buffs. Yelan offers incredible off-field Hydro application and ramping damage bonuses. Zhongli provides an unbreakable shield that completely negates the need to dodge, fundamentally changing the game's combat mechanics. Having even one of these characters drastically reduces the difficulty of the game.</p>

      <h2>The S Tier: The Core of the Abyss Roster</h2>
      <p>The S Tier is populated by incredibly strong characters who are slightly less universal than the SS tier but are still dominant forces in the Spiral Abyss. This tier is notable because it contains some of the best 4-star characters in the game, proving that you do not need to spend money to build elite teams.</p>

      <p>Bennett, Xingqiu, and Xiangling—often referred to as the "National Team" core—have been in the S Tier since the game's release in 2020. Bennett provides unparalleled attack buffs and healing, Xingqiu offers fast Hydro application and damage reduction, and Xiangling's Pyronado is one of the most powerful off-field abilities in the game. These 4-stars out-damage and out-support the vast majority of limited 5-star characters.</p>

      <p>The S Tier also houses the premier Main DPS characters who require specific teams to shine but offer incredible returns when properly supported. Alhaitham is a powerhouse for Spread/Hyperbloom teams, while Hu Tao remains the queen of single-target Vaporize damage. Navia brings Geo back into the meta with massive front-loaded burst damage, and Baizhu provides essential shielding and healing for Dendro reactions.</p>

      <h2>Understanding the Lower Tiers (A, B, and C)</h2>
      <p>It is crucial to understand that a character being in the A, B, or even C tier does not mean they are "bad." Genshin Impact is fundamentally a casual game, and every single character on the roster can be used to clear 99% of the overworld content and story quests. These lower placements specifically refer to their efficiency and ease of use in floor 12 of the Spiral Abyss.</p>

      <p><strong>A Tier</strong> characters are strong, viable units that usually require a bit more investment or very specific teammates to reach their full potential. For example, Ayaka and Nilou are incredible characters, but they are entirely restricted to Freeze and Bloom teams, respectively. If the Spiral Abyss features enemies immune to those reactions, their value plummets.</p>

      <p><strong>B Tier</strong> characters were often meta-defining in the past but have since been outclassed by newer units. Ganyu, Xiao, and Venti were the undisputed kings of the early game, but modern Abyss enemies have higher health pools, resist crowd control, and demand higher DPS ceilings than these older characters can easily provide without immense artifact investment.</p>

      <p><strong>C Tier</strong> characters generally have fundamental flaws in their kit, clunky mechanics, or completely lack synergy with the current reaction-based meta. Eula's physical damage is heavily resisted by modern enemies, and Dehya suffers from split-scaling and confusing defensive mechanics. While dedicated mains can certainly force these characters to work, it requires significantly more effort than simply using a higher-tier alternative.</p>

      <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
      <p>Understanding a Genshin tier list is ultimately about respecting your own time. When you pull a new character, you are committing to grinding talent domains, fighting world bosses, and suffering through the endless RNG of artifact farming. By consulting meta rankings, you can ensure that the weeks you spend building a character will actually result in a tangible upgrade to your account's power level.</p>

      <p>However, the most important rule of Genshin Impact supersedes any tier list: pull for the characters you actually enjoy playing. If you love a character's design, personality, or playstyle, you should absolutely build them, even if they are in the C tier. The meta is temporary, and the Spiral Abyss only rewards a few extra wishes a month. Finding joy in the combat system and exploring the world with your favorite characters is the true endgame.</p>

      <p>Use this tier list as a tool for optimization when you are struggling with difficult content, not as a rigid set of rules dictating how you must play the game. Build a solid foundation of top-tier supports, and you will have the freedom to play whatever main DPS your heart desires.</p>

      <div class="related-links">
        <h3>Explore More Tools</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/chatgpt-image-generator">Master AI Art with our ChatGPT Image Generator Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="/2-hour-timer">Set a 2-Hour Timer for your artifact farming sessions</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>


    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>Why are some 4-star characters ranked higher than 5-star characters?</summary>
        <p>In Genshin Impact, rarity does not always equal power. Several 4-star characters released at the game's launch (specifically Bennett, Xingqiu, Xiangling, and Fischl) have foundational kits that provide massive utility, off-field damage, and elemental application. They outclass many 5-stars because their abilities synergize perfectly with the core elemental reaction system.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need C6 4-stars or C1 5-stars to follow this tier list?</summary>
        <p>This tier list assumes C0 for limited 5-star characters and C0 for standard banner 5-stars. For 4-star characters, it assumes they have their most critical constellations (usually C2-C4) since they are much easier to obtain over time. However, top-tier units like Bennett and Xingqiu are still incredibly powerful even at C0.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why did my favorite character drop in the tier list this patch?</summary>
        <p>The Genshin meta revolves around the Spiral Abyss, which changes enemy lineups and buffs every patch. If the new Abyss features enemies with high resistance to your character's element, or if a new artifact set/support character drastically buffs a competing unit, your character's relative ranking will drop, even if their personal damage hasn't changed.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is it worth pulling for a weapon banner to make my character higher tier?</summary>
        <p>Generally, no. A character's signature 5-star weapon usually provides a 15-25% damage increase over their best 4-star or free-to-play option. However, pulling a new top-tier support character (like Nahida or Kazuha) will provide a much larger overall damage increase to your entire team than a single weapon upgrade.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I clear the Spiral Abyss with low-tier characters?</summary>
        <p>Yes, absolutely. Every character in Genshin Impact can clear floor 12 of the Spiral Abyss with enough investment in their artifacts, talents, and team synergy. Higher-tier characters simply make the process faster, require less optimal artifacts, and are more forgiving of player mistakes.</p>
      </details>

    </section>
  </div>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
